            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="level-1" class="zoom-level" data-level="1" aria-label="Local Group">
            <div class="visual"></div>
            <div class="level-content">
                <h2>The Local Group</h2>
                <p>Galaxies are not solitary islands. They cluster together, bound by gravity. This is our cosmic neighborhood, home to Andromeda, Triangulum, and our own Milky Way.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="level-2" class="zoom-level" data-level="2" aria-label="Andromeda Galaxy">
            <div class="visual"></div>
            <div class="level-content">
                <h2>Andromeda Galaxy</h2>
                <p>A majestic spiral, twice the size of the Milky Way, containing a trillion stars. It's on a collision course with us, but the cosmic dance won't begin for another 4.5 billion years.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="level-3" class="zoom-level" data-level="3" aria-label="Orion Nebula">
            <div class="visual"></div>
            <div class="level-content">
                <h2>Stellar Nursery</h2>
                <p>Within galaxies lie vast clouds of dust and gas, like the Orion Nebula. These are stellar nurseries, where intense gravity forges new stars and planetary systems from cosmic chaos.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="level-4" class="zoom-level" data-level="4" aria-label="A New Solar System">
            <div class="visual"></div>
            <div class="level-content">
                <h2>A New System</h2>
                <p>A young, fiery star ignites, its gravitational pull shaping the protoplanetary disk around it. From this dust and debris, new worlds are born, each with its own story.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="level-5" class="zoom-level" data-level="5" aria-label="The Journey Continues">
            <div class="level-content">
                <h2>The Journey Continues</h2>
                <p>From the infinitely large to the infinitesimally small, the patterns repeat. The universe is a story of scale, and this is just one path. The exploration is endless.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

    </main>

    <div id="ui-container">
        <div id="scroll-prompt">
            <p class="sr-only">Scroll to explore</p>
            <div class="scroll-prompt-icon" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        </div>
        <button id="reset-button">Restart Journey</button>
    </div>

    <div id="live-region" class="sr-only" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true"></div>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const universe = document.getElementById('universe');
            const zoomLevels = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.zoom-level'));
            const uiContainer = document.getElementById('ui-container');
            const scrollPrompt = document.getElementById('scroll-prompt');
            const resetButton = document.getElementById('reset-button');
            const liveRegion = document.getElementById('live-region');

            const ZOOM_FACTOR = parseFloat(getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--zoom-factor')) || 50;
            const NUM_LEVELS = zoomLevels.length;
            let currentLevel = 0;
            let isAnimating = false;

            function updateUniverse() {
                isAnimating = true;

                // Update classes and ARIA states
                zoomLevels.forEach((level, index) => {
                    level.classList.toggle('active', index === currentLevel);
                    level.setAttribute('aria-hidden', index !== currentLevel);
                });

                // Announce current level to screen readers
                const activeLevel = zoomLevels[currentLevel];
                const levelLabel = activeLevel.getAttribute('aria-label');
                if (levelLabel) {
                    liveRegion.textContent = `Now viewing: ${levelLabel}`;
                }

                // Calculate transforms
                const totalScale = Math.pow(ZOOM_FACTOR, currentLevel);
                const universeZ = currentLevel * -1000;
                universe.style.transform = `translateZ(${universeZ}px) scale(${totalScale})`;

                zoomLevels.forEach((level, index) => {
                    const levelScale = Math.pow(ZOOM_FACTOR, -index);
                    level.style.transform = `scale(${levelScale})`;
                    level.style.opacity = (index >= currentLevel) ? '1' : '0';
                });

                // Update UI visibility
                scrollPrompt.style.display = (currentLevel === 0) ? 'block' : 'none';
                resetButton.classList.toggle('visible', currentLevel > 0);
                uiContainer.classList.toggle('hidden', currentLevel === NUM_LEVELS - 1);

                setTimeout(() => {
                    isAnimating = false;
                }, parseFloat(getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--transition-speed')) * 1000);
            }

            function zoomIn() {
                if (currentLevel < NUM_LEVELS - 1) {
                    currentLevel++;
                    updateUniverse();
                }
            }

            function zoomOut() {
                if (currentLevel > 0) {
                    currentLevel--;
                    updateUniverse();
                }
            }

            function resetZoom() {
                currentLevel = 0;
                updateUniverse();
            }

            // Mouse wheel event
            let lastWheelTime = 0;
            window.addEventListener('wheel', event => {
                if (isAnimating) return;
                event.preventDefault(); // Prevent default page scroll
                const now = new Date().getTime();
                if (now - lastWheelTime < 50) return; // Simple throttling
                lastWheelTime = now;

                if (event.deltaY > 0) {
                    zoomIn();
                } else {
                    zoomOut();
                }
            }, { passive: false });

            // Keyboard navigation
            window.addEventListener('keydown', event => {
                if (isAnimating) return;
                if (event.key === 'ArrowDown' || event.key === 'PageDown') {
                    event.preventDefault();
                    zoomIn();
                }
                if (event.key === 'ArrowUp' || event.key === 'PageUp') {
                    event.preventDefault();
                    zoomOut();
                }
                if (event.key === 'Home') {
                    event.preventDefault();
                    resetZoom();
                }
            });

            // Reset button
            resetButton.addEventListener('click', resetZoom);

            // Initial setup
            function init() {
                // Set initial transform for each level so they appear nested
                zoomLevels.forEach((level, index) => {
                    const scale = Math.pow(ZOOM_FACTOR, -index);
                    level.style.transform = `scale(${scale})`;
                });
                // Set the first level as active
                zoomLevels[0].classList.add('active');
                liveRegion.textContent = `Now viewing: ${zoomLevels[0].getAttribute('aria-label')}`;
            }

            init();
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
